  "number": 6841,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/6841",
  "title": "feat(sortBy): support composition sorting strategies",
  "body": "**Summary**\r\n\r\nThis PR adds support to the `sortBy` widget for composition sorting strategies. The `items` parameter can hold objects with a `value` property (current) or objects with a `strategy` property (new, for compositions). Those properties are mutually exclusive. `value` still updates the index for a search request. However, `strategy` adds the `sortBy` parameter to the search request.\r\n\r\n**Result**\r\n\r\nIt requires using the `compositionClient` (`@algolia/composition`) instead of the `algoliasearch` client and passing a `compositionID` instead of an index. \r\n\r\nIn addition to the traditional index items with a `value` property, `sortBy` items can have a `strategy` property instead that references the composition sorting strategy created in the Algolia Merchandising Studio.\r\n",
